episodes.title: What we've learned from newly released Jeffrey Epstein files so far
episodes.description:
The Department of Justice has released hundreds of thousands of files related to the criminal prosecutions of convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein. CBS News justice reporter Jake Rosen has more.

episodes.title: What to expect from Ghislaine Maxwell grand jury materials if released
episodes.description:
A federal judge said that the Justice Department can release grand jury documents related to Ghislaine Maxwell's 2021 sex trafficking case. CBS News justice reporter Jake Rosen has more on what to expect.

episodes.title: Prince Andrew to lose real estate, titles, in unprecedented move from Buckingham Palace
episodes.description:
King Charles' brother, Prince Andrew, is being stripped of his royal titles, Buckingham Palace announced Thursday. He will now be known as Andrew Mountbatten Windsor. CBS News' Imtiaz Tyab and Julian Payne have more.
